posts.raw_content:
So I looked up which countries have the highest rates of autism. 

Wouldn't you know it, they just happen to be countries the CCP doesn't like so much. US, Japan, South Korea, Singapore (nuanced relationship but they're aligned with the US). Increased diagnosis may be due to methodologies, but they are what they are.

I then asked AI about which Vaccines or vaccine ingredients are imported from China. Brave AI didn't know. Grok however said this: 

"some raw materials or ingredients in pharmaceuticals, including potentially those used in vaccines, are sourced from China due to global supply chains. For specifics, check FDA listings."

When pressed it said:

"US pharma often relies on China for raw materials like antibiotics (e.g., neomycin in MMR or polio vaccines), aluminum salts (adjuvants in DTaP, HPV), and excipients like gelatin or stabilizers. For exacts, check FDA or manufacturer disclosures. Sources: GAO, Brookings."

Elevated levels of aluminum are found in the brains of people with autism, but large studies (a million people) haven't found a causal link. It might cause neuro inflammation, which in turn has an effect.

To conclude anything at this point would be a full blown bat shit crazy tinfoil hat conspiracy theory, and dumb, but that's what I found.
